ing, speaking, reading, writing and English test preparation skills.  These courses are:   Open to all. You do not need to be a UIC student.  Convenient. Study weekdays, evenings, weekend or online.  Focused on the skills that you need to improve.  Taught by experienced English instructors   Note: The Tutorium can issue the I-20 for students in full-time versions of these short-term courses.       Course Descriptions, Schedules and Fees   Don’t see what you’re looking for? We can create custom on-campus courses, online courses or private instruction to fit your needs. Contact us!      Conversation Skills         Course Info   This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve their speaking and listening skills in social, academic, and professional settings. You will learn strategies for effective communication as well as techniques for improving pronunciation. You will practice key vocabulary and American conversational expressions to help you feel more confident in social, academic and professional situations.  By the end of this course, you will be able to:   Successfully and appropriately engage in academic, professional, and casual conversations  Recognize the linguistic acts that occur in a variety of speaking situations, and be more comfortable participating in these types of interactions  Understand and begin to use the features of American English pronunciation for increased comprehension and to improve your speech clarity.   Dates and Times  Tuesdays and Thursdays 12:30 p.m. – 3 p.m. 5 weeks   Summer: May 19 – June 18   Note: The Tues./Thurs. section requires a free placement interview to join.  Request your online placement interview  Saturdays 9 a.m. – 12 p.m. 8 weeks   Summer: June 13 – Aug. 8 (no class 7/4)  Fall: Sept. 19 – Nov. 7   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $575 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.        Presentation Skills         Course Info   This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve comprehension and delivery of academic and professional presentations. You will develop an effective public speaking style to deliver complex information in an organized, professional manner, applying standard pronunciation features appropriately. You will also increase your ability to follow advanced academic lectures and professional presentations.  By the end of this course, you will be able to:   Display confidence while speaking to a group and in impromptu speaking situations  Organize and deliver a brief academic or professional presentation  Communicate ideas clearly by applying concepts of American English pronunciation  Identify strengths and weaknesses in a speech  Demonstrate comprehension of advanced academic lectures and professional talks   Dates and Times  Mondays and Wednesdays 12:30 p.m. – 3 p.m. 5 weeks   Summer: May  18 – June 17 (no class 5/25)   Note: The Mon./Wed. section requires a free placement interview to join.  Request your online placement interview  Wednesdays 6 p.m. – 9 p.m. 8 weeks   Summer: June 17 – Aug. 5  Fall: Sept. 16 – Nov. 4   Saturdays 9 a.m. – 12 p.m. 8 weeks   Summer: June 13  Aug. 8 (no class 7/4)  Fall: Sept. 19 – Nov. 7   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $575 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.        Pronunciation         Pronunciation   This course teaches pronunciation and speech modification techniques for non-native speakers of English. You will work one-on-one with an instructor to learn the keys to clear pronunciation: correct consonant and vowel sounds and American-style stress, rhythm, intonation, and pitch. To practice these elements, you will complete listening and recording assignments and receive personalized instructor feedback that identifies both where you need improvement and how to develop strategies for change.  By the end of this course, you will be able to:   Learn the pronunciation, intonation, and stress patterns of standard American English  Practice techniques and strategies to make your spoken English clearer and more effective  Build fluency and confidence in social and professional speaking situations.   Dates and Times  10 one-hour class sessions with a flexible schedule. (This is a private course. You and your instructor will select a convenient day and time. A shorter or longer course is possible. Please complete this form to sign up.)  Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $850 for 10 hours of private instruction  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before you want your first tutoring session to begin.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.        Effective Professional Writing         Effective Professional Writing   This course is designed to help non-native English speakers improve their ability to write more effective paragraphs and emails. You will learn to understand proper text organization and appropriately present arguments in writing in a clear, logical and organized manner. This course also helps you to understand and apply the rules of written English, and to find and correct your own grammar and punctuation errors in academic or professional writing tasks.  By the end of this course, you will be able to:   Produce register appropriate emails for various situations  Demonstrate understanding of text organization  Demonstrate the ability to write a highly effective, organized, unified, and well-developed persuasive paragraph  Demonstrate knowledge of your individual grammatical weaknesses and ways to address them.   Dates and Times  Tuesdays and Thursdays 9 a.m. – 11:30 a.m. 5 weeks   Summer: May 19 – June 18   Note: The Tues./Thurs. section requires a free placement interview to join.  Request your online placement interview  Mondays 6 p.m. – 9 p.m. 8 weeks   Summer: June 15 – Aug. 3  Fall: Sept. 14 – Nov. 2   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $575 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.        Online Grammar for Clear Writing         Course Info   This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the Blackboard learning management system to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from your instructor.  This course focuses on producing clear, error-free writing at the intermediate to advanced level. Your instructor will guide you through advanced grammar review, writing sample analysis, and development of effective self-editing techniques. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.  By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Identify weaknesses in your own and others’ writing  Make fewer errors in advanced grammatical structures  Use effective strategies for proofreading and editing your own work   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Course Fee  $400 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.        Online Developing Effective Writing         Course Info   This 5-week course is for intermediate to advanced level non-native speakers of English. It meets 100% online. There is no face-to-face classroom requirement. You use the Blackboard learning management system to view online assignments, participate in discussions, submit assignments, and receive feedback from the instructor.  This course focuses on how to produce concise, clear writing at the intermediate to advanced level.  You will learn techniques for starting a writing project, working with outlines, creating clear paragraphs, crafting introductions and conclusions, and adding concrete details. You work at your own pace and set your own deadlines, and you will receive detailed weekly feedback from your instructor.  By the end of the course, you will be able to:   Improve both paragraph and document organization  Be more confident with starting, revising, and concluding your writing  Clearly communicate ideas in a professionally written document   Dates and Times   Spring Term A: Jan. 17 – Feb. 14  Spring Term B: Feb. 28 – April 4  Summer Term A: May 29 – July 3  Summer Term B: July 10 – Aug. 14   Tuition and Registration  Fee  $400 Tuition includes all class materials.  Registration  The registration deadline is 1 week before classes begin. Late registration is possible if space permits. We limit class size, so please register early.  Ready to  enroll? Complete our online registration form.            Ready to enroll?  Register for your course today      Not sure what you need?  Request a free language assessment       Student Testimonials        “I’m adventure person and I like new experience, I chose to study at the Tutorium because I thought it would help me improve my English. Moreover, Chicago is a very beautiful and a lot of tourist places.”    Aline Pantano | Brazil              Request More Information  Contact us to learn more about our speaking and writing courses.   Request Info        